### New Report Endpoints Testing

#### POST /api/reports/employee - Employee Detailed Report
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports/employee \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "employeeName": "John Doe",
    "fromDate": "2026-03-01",
    "toDate": "2026-03-31"
  }'
```

Expected response includes:
- Employee info (name, jobTitle, department, baseSalary)
- All attendance records in period (date, actualStart, actualEnd, lateMinutes, overtimeMinutes)
- All absences in period (date, absenceType)
- All disciplinary actions in period (amount, reason, date)
- Payroll summary if exists (finalSalary, deductions, bonuses)

#### POST /api/reports/department - Department Summary Report
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports/department \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "departmentName": "IT Department",
    "fromDate": "2026-03-01",
    "toDate": "2026-03-31"
  }'
```

Expected response includes:
- Department info (name, officialStart, officialEnd)
- List of employees with:
  - name, jobTitle, baseSalary
  - total late minutes in period
  - total absence days in period
  - final salary if calculated
- Summary: total employees, total payroll cost, total late minutes

#### Export Functionality
Both new reports are exportable via the existing export endpoint:
```bash
# First generate the report
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports/employee \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "employeeName": "John Doe",
    "fromDate": "2026-03-01",
    "toDate": "2026-03-31"
  }' > employee_report.json

# Then export it
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports/export \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @employee_report.json \
  --output employee_report.csv
```
